# Email

MVP scope: transactional emails only via Resend. No editor, no campaigns, no Gmail OAuth. Post-launch (Phase 10+): festival → audience campaigns via the MailSurge-derived editor with Gmail/custom-domain connection.

## Templates (MVP)

All templates live in `src/emails/` as React Email components:

```
src/emails/
  layout/
    BaseLayout.tsx           — header, footer with unsubscribe + address
  invite-ambassador.tsx
  invite-org-member.tsx
  magic-link.tsx
  reward-earned.tsx
  reward-confirmed.tsx
  reward-fulfilled.tsx
  reward-reversed.tsx
  payout-sent.tsx
  payout-failed.tsx
  opportunity-assigned.tsx
  challenge-completed.tsx
  weekly-digest-ambassador.tsx
  weekly-digest-admin.tsx
  account-recovery.tsx
  integration-broken.tsx
```

Each template renders both HTML and plain-text alternative. Use `@react-email/render` with the `plainText: true` option for the alternative.

## Sending

Every send goes through `sendTransactional`:

```ts
async function sendTransactional(args: {
  to: { email: string; user_id?: string };
  template: TemplateId;
  organization_id?: string;  // for org branding (sender name, footer address)
  data: Record<string, unknown>;
  category: NotificationCategory;
  priority?: 'low' | 'normal' | 'high' | 'critical';
}): Promise<{ message_id: string } | { suppressed: true; reason: string }>;
```

Steps:
1. Look up `email_suppressions` for `sha256(lower(email))`. If suppressed for this category or globally → return `{ suppressed: true, reason }`. Do not send.
2. Look up `notification_preferences` for the user. If email channel disabled for this category → return `{ suppressed: true, reason: 'preference' }`.
3. Check `priority`. If `critical`, override quiet hours and category preferences.
4. Render template → { html, text }
5. Build email:
   - `from`: org-specific verified sender (default: `Ravo <noreply@ravo.fm>` or `<org-slug>@ravo.fm`)
   - `reply-to`: org-specific contact email if set
   - `subject`: from template
   - `headers`:
     - `List-Unsubscribe: <mailto:unsubscribe+{token}@ravo.fm>, <https://ravo.fm/u/{token}>`
     - `List-Unsubscribe-Post: List-Unsubscribe=One-Click`
     - `X-Entity-Ref-ID: {outbound_email_id}`
   - `text` and `html` both present
6. Send via Resend
7. Insert `outbound_emails` row with status `sent`
8. Return `{ message_id }`

## Deliverability (Gmail/Yahoo bulk sender compliance)

These are required from day one, not aspirational:

- **SPF, DKIM, DMARC** all configured for `ravo.fm` and any `*.ravo.fm` sender subdomains. DMARC policy at `p=quarantine` minimum (move to `p=reject` after stability).
- **One-click unsubscribe headers** on every send, even transactional. Gmail's bulk-sender requirements treat the absence as a spam signal.
- **Plain-text alternative** always present.
- **Bounce rate < 0.3%** — monitor via Resend webhooks, auto-suppress hard bounces.
- **Complaint rate < 0.1%** — monitor via webhooks, auto-suppress and log.
- **Authenticated From domain** — never spoof another domain.

## Suppression handling

Resend webhooks update suppression state:

```
event=bounce(hard) → email_suppressions.insert(email_hash, reason='bounced')
event=complaint   → email_suppressions.insert(email_hash, reason='complained')
event=unsubscribe → handled by /u/{token} endpoint, inserts row with reason='unsubscribed'
```

The unsubscribe link `https://ravo.fm/u/{token}` works for both one-click and standard unsubscribe. Token is a signed payload encoding `{ email_hash, category? }`. Optionally lets user choose specific categories via a preferences page after clicking.

## Outbound logging

`outbound_emails` rows track delivery lifecycle. Resend webhooks update `status` and `last_event_at`. Used by admin tooling to debug "did the ambassador get the email" questions.

PII: store `to_email_hash`, never plaintext. The body is not stored (templates + structured data = reproducible if needed).

## Senders

- Default: `Ravo <noreply@ravo.fm>` for all platform-level transactional emails (account recovery, etc.)
- Org-branded: `{Org Name} via Ravo <{org_slug}@ravo.fm>` for festival-related transactional emails (invites, reward updates)
- Post-MVP: festivals can connect their own Gmail OAuth or custom domain (SES, Postmark, or Resend with verified domain). Then `from` becomes the festival's own address. Until then, Ravo is the sender.

## Critical alerts override

If `priority = 'critical'`:
- Override quiet hours
- Override category preferences (the user signed up for service; broken-integration alerts must reach them)
- Still respect global unsubscribe (legal requirement)

Use sparingly. Only for: integration broken, payout failed, account compromised, mandatory legal notices.

## Testing

- A test-renderer script outputs every template to `tmp/email-previews/` for visual review
- Each template has a unit test asserting required fields render, unsubscribe link present, no PII in subject line
- Suppression check has an integration test: insert suppression, attempt send, assert blocked + logged
- Bounce/complaint webhooks have idempotency + signature tests

## Never do

- Send to a suppressed address
- Send marketing-style email pretending to be transactional (regulatory + spam signal risk)
- Store plaintext email body in DB
- Skip the `List-Unsubscribe-Post` header (Gmail bulk-sender requirement)
- Use a `from` address on a domain you don't control DNS for
- Embed tracking pixels in transactional emails (we use Resend's link/open tracking, which is opt-in per send and disabled by default for sensitive categories)

## Post-launch additions (Phase 10+)

When the email editor and campaigns ship:
- `email_campaigns`, `email_audiences`, `email_sends` tables
- The MailSurge editor lives at `src/components/admin/email-editor/`
- Gmail OAuth flow at `src/app/(admin)/[org]/settings/integrations/email/`
- Domain verification flow with DNS instructions
- Campaign-level suppression (separate from transactional, but global unsubs still respected)
- Send-test functionality
- Scheduling (use Inngest delayed events, not cron)

The infrastructure built for MVP (suppressions, preferences, outbound logging, deliverability) supports campaigns without rework.
